arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into three series: Commencement programs; Doctoral hooding ceremony; and Graduate School Commencement programs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains the commencement programs for Tufts College and later Tufts University and its schools which record all degree recipients including honorary and featured speakers. It includes commencement programs for undergraduate and graduate degrees beginning in 1857.

processinfo.head: Processing status
processinfo.p: This collection is processed and open for research

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Commencement Programs, 1857 -- 2021. Tufts University. Digital Collections and Archives. Medford, MA.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains commencement programs for Tufts College and later Tufts University and its schools. They record all degree recipients including honorary and featured speakers. The bulk of these programs include all schools bound in one volume.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This program was created for the 164th Commencement Ceremony, which was held on May 27, 2022 due to the Covid-19 pandemic.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Doctoral Hooding ceremony was initiated in 1998 in order to celebrate the accomplishments of students in Arts and Sciences who are receiving their doctorates. In 2006 candidates for the Occupational Therapy Doctorate graduated for the first time. Also in 2006 the name of the ceremony was changed from Ph.D. Hooding to Doctoral Hooding.
